		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Ok here is the scoop on this quest. I know what your talking about with the dwarf. I myself have looked for him several times near the roost. A bit of advice, skip it, its not really needed. Go into seafares roost and wait for an npc that looks like a madman like the other posts says. Get yourself 4 drom champaines (no longer lore), when he pops hail him and give him the 4 droms one at a time. After each one you can hail him again if needed, he shouldnt despawn, but its safer this way. After you give him the 4th drom he should give you a blanket. Now you need to take the blanket to a prisoner below the arena in wfp. Before you do this though, make sure you get 1 bog juice you can buy one at most alcohol merchants you will also need to make 1 edible goo. Easy to make even without baking skill. Get yourself 1 firebeetle eye, and 1 rat ear.. get yourself a few of these in case of fails. Make your edible goo and head to see the prisoner. Hail him and he says something incoherent. Give him the blanket, he then says something else like: &quot;Bog and goo&quot;, give him the bog juice and edible goo at the same time. He will then give you a key. You need to take this key to the banker in Highpass Hold. When you go downstairs there you will see the banker off to your right just around the corner. Give her the key and you will get a sealed letter. You need to take this letter to Brother Hayle down in Splitpaw in South Karanas. Do not, I repeat do not go there alone, bring at least one other person with you (preferably with invisible spell), you need to go all the way to the jail cells there. Brother Hayle is all the way in the last cell. There are two splitpaw gnoll prisoners with him there. Make sure your faction is high enough.. You need to be kindly or higher with the Temple of Life (Paladin faction for Qeynos) in order for this to work. You can either do this before or after you get all the items to turn into Hayle. Its up to you. When you give him the sealed letter, he will return to you a Note that says return this with the brilliant sword of faith, hilt, and your testemony of truth letter. He will then give you the Soulfire sword. Now after you have done this, You need to either head to Mistmoore castle or west freeport with a good group for friends or guildmates. I will start with Mistmoore first, its the easier of the two. After you get into Mistmoore zone, head down to the graveyard. Fighting mobs the whole way I might add. Now after you get to graveyard go all the way to your left hand side once your past the gate, head all the way to the wall straight ahead. There is a Shadowman there.. do not kill him. You will ruin faction with The Temple of Solesk Ro if you do. After reaching wall turn to your left and go through hidden wall. This the the way to jail cells. Once your in the cell area you need to open the door straight ahead after you go through the second secret wall. This will open all the cell doors.. fight all mobs, starting with casters first if there are any. Once that is done there is another hidden wall to the left of the first door you opened go up the staircase again fighting mobs the whole way up, until you reach a room with two gargoyles kill them and camp the room. You are looking for an npc troll named Xict, he drops the Hilt, his placeholder is a Mistmoore guard, now this sometimes takes awhile for him to spawn. Sometimes several hours. Ok now that you have the hilt its off to fight Sir Lucan, you will need to have a good group of at least 8 or 9 lvl 40+ characters to help out. Sir lucan is stationed in the milita house, once in the door there take a left. follow that all the way down to the other guard there. There is a door on your left, go in and go through the next door, If lucan is up he will be standing by Brother Jentry. You need someone not kos to pull lucan out and run to area near the right tent. All other players helping should be up against the brick wall waiting. Now whoever pulls should run through zone. Have another player not kos hail Lucan until all other guards leave the area, after the person that zoned can zone back in and wait by wall with the others..now when its all clear of guards except lucan proceed to attack. Once killed another lucan will spawn, an undead one. Kill him and loot for his note. Take the tunnels to North fp and go to the Paladin guild..not the big ivory looking cleric/paladin guild, but the smaller one, go all the way to the top and to the back and talk to the npc there...I cant remember his name, but he is all the way to the rear of building, standing by railing. Hail him and talk to him to make sure you have the right one.. he will speak of Lucan. Give him the note you got off of Lucan and you will recieve your brilliant sword of faith. Now turn in all the items to Hayle to get your soulfire. Good luck my fellow Paladin, and may the healing light of Rocent Nife bless you in your endeavors. <br>  <br> Aamadanae Whirlwind <br> 43rd Paladin of the Knights of Burning Justice and council member to the Phoenix Legion		

